deck_excerpt: Dragon Shrine, send BAckground Drag to GY, then SS it back along with a dragon from your hand, link into Hieratic, then SS Draco, Activate Quick Launc
deck_description:
OK! This deck might not be the PUREST of decks like I suggested up above, but it's SOOO hard to build a 100% Guardragon deck that's good. I had to add in some things. Basically what this deck does is sending Justiacia to the gy along with background Drag via dragon shrine, then SS Background along with 1 lvl 4 or lower frmo your hand (you should have a level 4 or lower.). Once you SSed the Background and the Lvl 4 or lower, send Promeneses from your hand to the GY (If you have Promineses) to trigger it's effect WHEN a nomal monster leaves the field. Then linking into hieratic spheres. Afterwards, if you didn't send Promineses to the GY via it's OWN effect, you should have Crusadia Draco (Ik, here's a crusadia, But honestly, it's against the law to not add it in, SOrry :3), or quick launch or whatever that'll summon a dragon. From there on it's just linking into Elpy, then if you have the following cards in your hand, follow the following precedures:

Draco (If you didn't use it's effect to summon itself to link into Elpy,) SS it next to a link monster's zone. Link using the draco and hieratic into agarpain. Agarpain's effect Summons Crystal wing. (Also, there's an alternative,) After you SS draco, Normal Summon a dragon, as I don't think you have normal Summoned yet, then use hieratic, draco and the normal summoned monster to link into saryuja. You won't get the draw effect, but it's good. Activate Elpy, Summoning Red-Eyes Darkness Metal from your hand/deck, then SS 1 dragon from your GY or hand using Darkness Metal's effect. Then use Darkness and the SSed dragon (Darkness Metal summoned) to link into agarpain, afterwards, agarpain summoned Crystal Wing, Then you can go for a Link Summon of a Link 4, then if you have the right cards and if you play the right cards in the right way, you SHOUL be able to summon at least 1 more Synchro monster. SHOULD!!!

World Legacy Guardragon, activate it, summon a dragon if you want to, then move Elpy to the zone DIRECTLY BENEATH Hieratic to trigger it's effect, which will summon Darkness Metal, then activate Darkness to SS a drag from hand or gy, then, either: 1) Use all 4 monsters to Link into Saryuja. 2) Use every monster except Elpy. Both will work, for No.1, Saruja will draw 4 cards, then shuffle 3 into the deck (Also!!!! I would not suggest using all monsters, except Elpy for the link summon of Saryuja if you do not have a monster in your hand that can be SSed by Saryuja's effect.) | (If you have no monsters you can SS using Saryuja's effect before the draw, and you draw a SS-Able monster, shuffle the not needed cards into the deck), No.2 Saryuja SSes a monster from your hand, if you can, if not, you're stuffed.

Alright, that's about it, also if you get a really lucky hand, you SHOULD be able to summon Crystal Wing, Borreload Savage/F.A. Dawn Dragster ("/" because I don't think you can Summon both, I've tried, and I could only Summon 1 of them) and a Link 4. Good Luck! Thank you for viewing my deck!

deck_description: Nelson Andrews, known as Fuya Okudaira (奥平風也, Okudaira Fūya) in the Japanese version, is a child actor and one of the "Number" holders in Yu-Gi-Oh! ZEXAL. Nelson uses a Sparrow Family Deck, based on the characters from his TV series. It is capable of quickly swarming the field and Summoning "D. D. Esper Star Sparrow", a card based on the character he himself plays. When the whole Sparrow Family gathers, Nelson can use "Change to Jet Iron" to combine them into "D. D. Jet Iron". His "Number", "Galaxy Queen", is based on the character his mother plays on his TV series. The influence of it convinced him it actually was his mother, so he goes to great lengths to defend it with cards such as "Furious Max's Curse" and "Star Sparrow Forever". After "Galaxy Queen" is absorbed by Astral, Nelson utilizes "Galaxy Queen's Light" to Xyz Summon "Superdimensional Robot Galaxy Destroyer".

The Signer Dragons are a series of Level 7 and 8 Dragon Synchro Monsters introduced in Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's.
deck_description: The Signer Dragons are a series of Level 7 and 8 Dragon Synchro Monsters introduced in Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's. These legendary dragons play a part in the legend of the Crimson Dragon, as well as being connected to the Signers themselves. That connection being that these legendary beasts, who actually joined forces with the Crimson Dragon, were the ones who sealed an evil within the Nazca Lines. That very same evil, now known as the "Earthbound Immortals", reappeared once again in the world as Duel Monsters cards used by the Dark Signers. Every Signer Dragon has been featured in the anime and has been released in the OCG/TCG. They are: "Stardust Dragon", "Red Dragon Archfiend", "Black Rose Dragon", "Ancient Fairy Dragon", "Black-Winged Dragon" and "Life Stream Dragon". In the anime, Professor Fudo gave the "Stardust Dragon", "Red Dragon Archfiend" and "Black Rose Dragon" cards to Rex Goodwin. These cards were originally designed so that their corresponding Signer could activate the safety switches for the Ener-D system.

All "Infernity" cards are Unlimited in Trinity Format.
Massive revival power
Can make Extra Deck monsters and Negates with ease
deck_description:
Rating: 6/10

Strengths: 

  • All "Infernity" cards are Unlimited in Trinity Format.
  • Massive revival power
  • Can make Extra Deck monsters and Negates with ease

Weaknesses:

  • Deck relies on a lot of setup
  • Deck can run out of gas quickly

Trinities:

  • Infernity Launcher (Extra Unlimited Card)
  • Infernity Archfiend (Extra Unlimited Card)

Comments:

  • Don't be sickened by the Infernity General. He's there to make Level 8 Synchros with Infernity Avenger, and is never a brick.
  • Infernity Launcher can deal 7500 damage:
    • Activate Infernity Launcher, Summoning Infernity General and Infernity Necromancer (1).
    • Use Infernity Necromancer's effect to Summon Infernity Archfiend (2).
    • Infernity Archfiend Searches Infernity Launcher.
    • Make LANphorhynchus with Archfiend and Necromancer.
    • Activate Infernity Launcher, Summoning Infernity Archfiend and another Infernity Archfiend (3).
    • 1800 + 1800 + 2700 + 1200 = 7500
  • Variants of the above combo are possible with different GY setup. Searching Launcher in the End Phase off of an Archfiend can make it a full OTK.
  • Fusion Destiny here is used to refill the hand with Destiny HERO - Celestial and Destiny HERO - Disk Commander, as well as being another way to mill Infernity Archfiend.

deck_description:

  • Lots of search power
  • Lots of searchable interaction

Weaknesses:

  • Bad openings will always lose to negation
  • Graveyard removal on Hanzo hurts
  • Decks playing lots of backrow removal have an advantage vs this

Trinities:

  • Upstart Golden Ninja (Extra Unlimited Card)
  • Ninja Grandmaster Hanzo(Extra Unlimited Card)
  • Reinforcement of the Army (Extra Unlimited Card)

Comments:

  • Ideal Turn 1 play is to either:
    • Setup Ninja Grandmaster Hanzo and Ninjitsu Art of Super-Transformation, To make Yellow Dragon Ninja or Omni Dragon Brotaur, who can search for Dark Armed Dragon.
    • Use Upstart Golden Ninja to search Ninja Grandmaster Hanzo, search Twilight Ninja Getsuga, the Shogun, Make Ninja Grandmaster Saizo, Set Ninjitsu Art Notebook, Discard Twilight Ninja Getsuga, the Shogun, setting Hidden Village of Ninjitsu Arts and a Revival Trap to use on Twilight Ninja Getsuga, the Shogun. If all goes to plan, you can make Borreload Dragon next turn.

Not as good consistent as the other deck but its pretty fun. You could probably also keep in the cards I removed from the other deck and play a 60 card (or just 50ish card) variant. Heres my other deck that explains the strategy and combos of the deck: https://ygoprodeck.com/a-to-z-ojama-deck/

deck_excerpt: Dinosaurs dont use extra monster zone so much so i mixed them with invoked and got this.
the most consistent and BIG BRAIN an ojama deck can get
deck_description:
Contrary to popular belief, ojamas are actually BIG BRAIN deck that rely on BIG BRAIN COMBOS that require BIG BRAIN to pull off. This deck is one of my favorites of all time due to my love for ojamas and THE CHAZZ. That being said, however, it most certainly isn't the most competitive deck out there but it sure as hell is fun. The main goal of the deck is to turbo out A-to-Z Dragon Buster Cannon with as many cards as possible in your hand so you can negate everything your opponent does. The most important card in the entire deck is Saryuja Skull Dread. It was like it was made to be played in this deck. Without it, this deck would be GARBAGE. That being said, this deck cannot play through negation much at all. If Saryuja or other combo plays get negated and you have no response (called by the grave), you're donzo. The three easiest ways to get this bad boy out are the Ojamatch + Ojamagic combo, Tri-wight, and Ojamassimilation on ABC-Buster Dragon. The best opening hand you can hope for is the first combo. By using Ojamatch on Ojamagic you are able to search for Ojama Red and Armed Dragon LV3 and able to normal summon the dragon immediately after for free. Ojamagic's effect then activates, enabling you to add Ojama Yellow, Ojama Green, and Ojama Black directly to your hand. Bam, you just got four monsters to your hand and one on your field without your normal summon. How is that fair? Well it doesn't even end there. You can then normal summon Ojama Red and activate it's effect to special summon your other three ojamas from your hand to the field. Link away your four ojamas to summon Saryuja Skull Dread to draw four cards. The main cards you are looking for are Ojamassimilation, Tri-wight, and Ojama Pajama (if you dont have one already). Situationally, there can be many cards you want depending on what you already have. The main cards you want to get rid of are first off any of the six union bricks you play in the deck, any original ojama cards you need in the deck in order to activate Ojamagic (if you dont have one of each yellow, black, or green ojamas in your deck, ojamagic cant activate), and possibly hand traps if you already have enough ojama's/ojamassimilations to make A-to-Z Dragon Buster Cannon (precicely two Ojamassimilation and six ojama monsters in your hand/field/graveyard). Since Saryuja is a broken card and isnt once per turn (actually, almost every single card in this deck isnt once per turn), you can use it's draw effect again by summoning another! After Summoning Saryuja there are two cards that can extend your plays even more by summoning YET ANOTHER Saryuja. First off, Tri-Wight can summon Ojama Yellow, Ojama Green, and Ojama Black back from the grave directly to the field, allowing you to easily summon YET ANOTHER Saryuja by linking off the three ojamas and the Armed Dragon LV3 you summoned earlier. The other method of summoning YET ANOTHER Saryuja is by using Ojamassimilation on ABC-Dragon Buster by banishing the three original ojamas from the graveyard to special summon A-Assault Core, B-Buster Drake, and C-Crush Wyvern. You are then able to link off the three union monsters and the aforementioned Armed Dragon to make YET ANOTHER Saryuja. You see, the reason you are able to do this is because you can special summon ABC-Dragon Buster by banishing the three union monsters from the field OR the graveyard, which I didn't know when I first started playing this deck and when I found out, MORE SARYUJAS!!!! Normally, The deck can't consistently pull off this combo right away every game so two important cards to open so you can search out the combo starters are Ojama Blue and Ojama Pajama. If you are going first and brick (which lets be honest is going to happen most of the time), just set one, or if you have two, both of these cards face down and pass. If your opponent runs over and destroys your Ojama Blue by battle (and only battle, nothing else) you are able to add TWO ojama cards from your deck to your hand. The main two cards you want are the obvious Ojamatch/Ojamagic BUT if you already have one, or both, Ojamassimilation is your next priority or Ojama Pajama if you dont already have one. Another really handy card you can search out is Ojama Delta Hurricane which can really come in handy to just wipe your opponents board completely. Activate Ojama Pajama on your opponent's turn to search out Ojamagic and discard it to get the three ojamas. If you already have Ojamagic in your hand, FANTASTIC. You can instead search any card you need (Ojamassimilation) and discard the Ojamagic already in your hand to +4. You Can then use Ojama Pajama's again on your turn (this is one of the only once per turn cards but you can use it on either player's turn so its NICE). I dont have the card, but Apollousa Bow of the Goddess basically has the same requirement as Saryuja Skull Dread and is basically the same card as A-to-Z Armed Dragon Cannon so if you have it I think you need to include it. I guess you can include Borrelsword Dragon too if you also include 2 other Link Spider and a Missus Radiant. When you normal summon your red to summon the other 3 ugli bois you can make 2 link spiders then link those two into the missus then link another spider THEN make the dragon. I dont have a sword dragon. Dont play this deck if you don't have at least 2 Saryuja's. If you want to play a more casual/fun/cheaper deck, play the Armed Dragon Catapult Cannon version. Not as good but more CHAZZ. Pros of the deck:
  • cool as hell
  • ojamas
  • fun
  • big brain
  • no one expects the ojama
  • the chazz
Cons of the deck:
  • Potentially EVERY card in the deck can be a brick. ALL OF THEM. They need each other to survive. This deck emphasizes the power of teamwork and friendship.
  • Luck based mostly
  • Cant fight through negates well
  • If your pieces get banished other than your own effects, you best hope you can just beat over your opponent with saryuja's
THANKS FOR READING MY EXPLANATION IF YOU DID. If you have any questions about my explanation or dissagree with me please let me know, I love learning new things about yugioh and getting better.

deck_excerpt: Gren Maju Da Eiza Mystic Mine (Going Second) (Post July 2019 Banlist)
deck_description: Alright so I've been testing this deck idea for a while now and this build I came up with from scratch works really well. I know a lot of you guys would really enjoy playing this deck because it is a lot of fun to play and disrupts your opponent constantly. This deck likes to go second but it can also go first, the goal of the deck is to use Mystic Mine to stall your opponent until you get enough banished cards to get Gren Maju's attack up to 10,000 or up so you can attack into one of your opponent's monsters for game. What really locks in your win is waiting for your opponent to make a link monster that way next turn you can use Mystic Mine to stall and attack for game with Gren Maju when you have enough banished cards because link monsters can't go into defense and your opponent most likely won't be able to get rid of the link monster so you can just kill them with Gren Maju. The deck did really well in testing and when going second is also to easily disrupt your opponent's plays with Mystic Mine and hand traps. The extra deck is composed of mainly Ghost Reaper & Winter Cherries targets since it is a very strong card when it resolves. The reason for two of each of most of the extra deck cards is because of Pot of Extravagance. It is most likely that you will banish only one of each and not two which could potentially screw you over from not having the right Cherry targets left in the extra deck. I hope you guys enjoy this one, and stick around for more!

deck_name: Hero full power July 2019 post banlist
deck_excerpt:
Meta oriented Hero deck at full power, post july 2019 banlist.
A review of the gameplay is available here : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEFOVMBVQ
deck_description: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEFOVMBVQug 2019 is definitively the year of heroes, at the time I post this deckAirman came back to 2 and we had Vision Hero support that add a lot of consistancy and more spam power to the deck to play more easily under hand traps and negations. So actually Hero can play excellent disruptive monsters if starting first and have a great facility to OTK the opponent thanks to it's ability to search into the deck and summon incredible beatsticks like Trinity Hero Vision. The other big boost comes from new Hero Vision Faris And Hero Vision Increase that can set up the Graveyard while making a board of 3 monsters without consuming the normal summon and only starting with 1 Faris in hand. Faris will of course be at 3 being the best starter of the deck, and Increase at 2 to limit chances of having it in the starting hand and prevent the loop from being broken if having one. A little complicated sentence but in fact a logical ratio. The discard cost of Faris's effect can be a good point to send a Malicious to the graveyard since we absolutely don't want to have it in the starting hand, or trigger the tuto effect of Shadow Mist in some situations. Main deck we'll of course play 2 Elemental Hero Airman to search the integralty of the deck's monsters and eventually clean the backrow if the starting hand allows to go without it's principal effect. Elemental Hero Solid Soldier, Hero Vision Vyon and Elemental Hero Shadow Mist are at 2 too, because more could be bricky, knowing that we now have 2 more tutos in the presence of Airman. We play a package of destiny heroes with Malicious, Celestial, Dynatag and Plasma respectively at x2 and x1 to gain spam potential with Vyon and abuse Dystopia effect while having a stable draw power if there is a second turn. Plasma here is more playable than ever due to the facility of spam and consists on a good floodgate-like to finish your turn while starting first, especially if you can summon Dark Law during opponent's turn. Finally Elemental Hero Honest Neos can bring a +2500 Atk boost to bypass almost every beatsicks and easily and perform solid OTKs. Ash Blossom and Called By The Grave are almost recurring today and prevent opponent from breaking a crucial loop or slow him down by striking a starter or a key effect in the middle of a combo. On the side of spells, we play a fusion package with 1 Polymerization and the 3 Mask Change, 1 will be sufficient since it's searchable and having one in hand is often a deadweight since we have less cards to conduct loops and this is used in the last plays of the Main Phase. Fusion Destiny is an amazing stater due to its capacity of sending the fusion materials in the graveyard directly from the deck (be aware, it can be stopped by Ash Blossom) and is useful to summon a Dystopia and send Malicious or Dynatag regarding your hand, to have an instant link 2 (mostly Xtra Hero Cross Crusader than can resurrect the Dystopia previously used as link mterial or a malicious to sacrifice it and trigger the tuto effect). Destiny Draw is another way to discard a dead Malicious, Dynatag or Celestial that are not needed and far better in the graveyard, and is generally a good way to draw. Finally A Hero Live and E are good free summon to instantly chain a tuto effect or a way to search specific pieces of combos.   The extra deck runs a specific tech adapted to the actual metagame with Abyss Dweller that hits hardly a good number of decks preventing effects that trigger in the graveyard, and may be used as material to go on Masked Hero Acid that can clean an entire backrow and facilitate otks with it's little dropping effect. Besides we have a classic Xtra Hero package with Wonder Driver to recycle Mask Change, Cross Crusader to assemble combos with more consistance and revive key monsters like Destiny Hero Dystopia, and lastly Dread Decimator that can simply give a great stats boost to itself and pointed monsters (max. 3) to bust OTKs and break through beatsticks more easily. Is an important monster, especially if starting first, thanks to it's ability to be summoned by Destiny Fusion and revived by Cross Crusader to quick destroy opponent's cards while it's attack differs than it's original one, thing that is easily to set up thanks to Dynatag and Dread Decimator. Destiny Hero Dominance is used to send 3 monsters to the graveyard in specific cases and can defend or support battle phases with its revive-like effect. Vision Hero Adoration is a monster that can easily reduce ATk's monsters to 0 to blow your opponent's LP with Vision Hero Trinity that is a great OTK generator since your opponent has monsters, because during the summon turn it's Atk goes to 5000 without boosts and it can perform 3 attacks on monsters (Dread Decimator can easily bring a +1000 and Neos a +2500). Masked Hero Anki can finish the opponent with a direct attack and tuto Mask Change if destryed a monster by battle to instantly trigger it and fusion a Masked Hero Dark Law on Anki to continue attacking the opponent. Dark Law is an excellent anti meta card to summon while going first, having a Macro Cosmos-like effect and punishing the opponent's tutos by banihing a random card from his hand. Dian may be summoned on Solid Soldier to trigger it's effect and spam the board while being able to summon low level Heroes from the deck. Lastly Tornado Dragon is a way to deal with opponent's backrow to ensure some OTKs.

deck_name: Golden Castle of Gren Maju Gimmick Deck
deck_excerpt: A deck that utilises Golden Castle of Stromberg and Gren Maju for a strong late game and many trap cards for consistent negation.
deck_description:
Use Golden Castle of Stromberg Hexe Trude for on-demand removal, and to banish cards for Gren Maju. Orochi is mainly for banishment and stalling (though it can also be used with Hexe Trude to Xyz Summon a Rank 8.). Eater of Millions for easy removal and high ATK late game. The rest is mostly negation or draw cards.

Megafleet Dragon is in the ED in case you go against a Cyber Dragon deck.

 

(note: despite the goal of using Gren Maju for high ATK, I find myself winning with Hexe Trude much more often, due to the inconsistencies of Gren Maju. Don't be afraid to simply swarm with Hexe Trude to win.)

deck_excerpt: Easy deck master access
deck_description:
The deck Is changed and I tried to make in the cheapest/ good way.  
Main/Extra Deck: The big news here is the Salamangreat Almiraj is super easy to summon with any krawler with -1000 ATK and he points to your field. That way you can use Foolish Burial Goods or Plaeozoic Marrella to dump and banish World Legacy Mind Meld. And thats it, Deus X-Krawler on your field and almiraj protecting against any card with destructive effects, the rest is bonus. Crusadia Krawler and the Paleozoics on the deck is useful to bring out Paleozoic Anomalocaris which having any trap as material, he can destroy cards on the field in both turns as a quick effect, it responds Mystic Mine. Phantom Knights of Cursed Javelin selects a monster to negate his effect, reducing his attack to zero. You can counter timelords, gren maju or any maniac monster. The most important thing to do in this deck is flip deus krawler face up, so, you can bring Ghostrick Angel of Mischief with 2 level 2 to search Ghostrick Scare if you don't have World Legacy Pawns. Totalizes 4 cards for flipping in the whole deck. Heavy Storm Duster, Imperial order and Unending Nightmare on main deck helps to deal with dark magician, witchcraft, exodia or any spell/trap based decks to not get caught off-guard in a single. Recall and Compulsory Evacuation Device messes-up with monsters and his special summons. I put only one Crusadia Krawler to give you the krawler support cards and combo with XYZ/Links without bricking your draw. World Legacy Survivor  can dump cards that you seriously need in your next DP and World Legacy - World Armor can easily brick your hand alone (your opponent will attack in the most cases at his very beginning and flipping by battle doesn't trigger the armor. Also the world legacy pawns doesn't trigger the armor too). I already used survivor with worm bait before, its very sinergizing and recommended but too vulnerable for most newer decks. And recently I removed the lightning kaiju because it was bricking/ drawing it and when I use it, make things hard once the field spell is not active. The deck is focused on removal, this way its possible to win without swarming, otherwise make sure to use Krawler Glia, Krawler Ranvier and X-Krawler Qualiark asap.  
Side Deck: Deep Dark Trap Hole, Network Trap Hole and Black Horn of Heaven can disrupts your opponent's field even more with compulsory and recall on the main deck. Also you can avoid some hand traps or any other special summoned monster with Chain Hole/ Lost Wind. Grave of the Super Ancient Organism stops all level 6 higher monsters on the field from working, deus krawler passively negates all other monsters making a complete match with this one. Dark Bribe Totalizes with the others spell/ trap destroyers in the main deck.  
Dragun, Raidraptor Ultimate Falco, Balerdroch is countering deus krawler? Don't expect to win over them it but avoiding it. Don't let your opponent bring him. Return monsters back to his hand or remove then from play and if he try again to activate their monsters, make sure Deus X-Krawler is face up this time, may the World Legacy In Shadow protect you. If you still lose, trying is a merit by its own. Be safe.

deck_excerpt: Prevents special summons, win with Vanity's Fiend or Obelisk.
deck_description: Prevents your opponents special summons by rushing out Vanity's Fiend. Designed to counter most decks which rely heavily on special summoning monsters from the deck. Most of these decks have little removal apart from their monsters which they need to special summon, so with Vanity's Fiend we can heavily deny the opponent from most of their deck's capabilities. Considering adding Spell Canceller and more Jinzo's to further deny the opponent and protect Vanity's Fiend, which would also be good against Exodia decks.
